column4: What age group do you belong to?

column9: 01) My job offers me the opportunity to develop myself.
column10: 02) My immediate supervisor is supportive of my efforts.
column11: 03) My relationship with my supervisor is a harmonious one.
column12: 04) My immediate supervisor has ideas that are helpful to me and my group-work.
column13: 05) This organization is willing to improve, given the chance.
column14: 06) I am personally in agreement with the stated goals of my work unit.
column15: 07) The leadership of this organization will help it progress.
column16: 08) The company has a strong inter-departmental collaboration culture.
column17: 09) Evidence of a prior TQM initiative exists and a clear success picture is observable.
column18: 10) I have the information that I need to do a good job.
column19: 11) This organization is introducing enough new policies and procedures.
column20: 12) I understand the purpose of this organization.
column21: 13) Orientation given to newly-hired employees include quality training and monitoring.
column22: 14) This organization's leadership efforts result in the Company's fulfilment of its purpose.
column23: 15) My relationship with members of my work group are friendly, as well as, professional.
column24: 16) We have quality teams (i.e. quality improvement teams) with activities for continuous improvement.
column25: 17) I am sure the quality teams are adding value to our clients' satisfaction.
column26: 18) The organization has adequate mechanisms for binding itself together for continuous improvement.
column28: 20) The priorities of this organization are understood by its employees.
column29: 21) There is willingness by management to critically examine the existing organizational system.
column30: 22) It is clear to me why my boss tries to guide my work efforts.
column31: 23) I have established the relationship that I need to be able to do my job properly.
column32: 24) A "TQM Success Roadmap" exists in the company.
column33: 25) Other work units are helpful to my work unit whenever assistance is requested.
column34: 26) The company’s supply base, customer base or the social systems upon which it depends are fairly diversified
column35: 27) The company's Business Continuity Plan clearly identifies contingency measures to deploy in case its operations experience worst case scenario(s)
column36: 28) Clients now ask for evidence (i.e. certification, awards) of our quality management system.
column37: 29) I understand my boss’ efforts to help me and co-workers improve.
column38: 30) The company's business structure is modular allowing rapid rewiring especially during crisis.
column39: 31) There are clear and concrete measures for TQM success in the company.
column40: 32) This organization’s planning and control efforts are helpful in its growth and development.
column41: 33) This organization has the ability to change.
column42: 34) The Company executives provide the leadership necessary for change.
column43: 35) Management communicates quality directions extensively throughout the organization by actions as well as words.
column44: 36) The company recognizes the need for backups even at the expense of short-term efficiency.
column45: 37) There is a written business strategy that includes vision and/or mission statements.
column46: 38) The company's "Quality Policy" articulates the commitment to excellence and the importance of customer satisfaction.
column47: 39) The business strategy statement is widely communicated company-wide.
column48: 40) General assembly meetings are conducted at least twice a year wherein the results of the strategic planning is shared.
column49: 41) The business strategy is clearly defined to provide adequate direction for all areas of business.
column50: 42. The strategic planning process addresses internal factors (conditions the company can control) that significantly affect the business.
column51: 43) The company continuously measures its products, services and practices in comparison with its toughest competitors within and outside the industry.
column52: 44) Information about competitors is used to identify "best practices" and establish performance benchmarks.
column53: 45) The benchmarking process is used throughout the organization to identify operational improvements and to establish effective goals and objectives.
column54: 46) Benchmarks are periodically reviewed and re-calibrated to ensure that latest developments in "best practices" and performance achievements are recognized.
column55: 47) The company's strategies encourage the in-house development of important competencies and technologies.
column56: 48) The strategy statements are used by management as means of developing the business plan.
column57: 49) The strategic planning process addressed external factors (conditions that the company cannot control) that signficantly affect the business.
column58: 50) The company shared with all its employees its mission and vision.
